        <h2 id="recipe1">Recipe #1: Spaghetti-Hs</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 15 min</li>
            <li>Serves: 65</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td class="ingredient">Spaghetti shaped Hs</td>
                    <td>200 lbs</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class="ingredient">Marinara Sauce</td>
                    <td>300 gal</td>   
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class="ingredient">Salt</td>
                    <td>40 lbs</td>   
                </tr>                
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Put all ingredients into a 600 gal vat.
</p>
        <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Heat on high heat for 10 min, stir entire time.
</p>
        <p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Let sit and cool for 5 min, then serve.
</p>
<a href="#Contents">Back to Contents</a>
        <h2 id="recipe2">Recipe #2: PB&J</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 30 sec</li>
            <li>Serves: 1</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td class="ingredient">Bread</td>
                    <td>2 slices</td>
                </tr>
                    <tr>
                    <td class="ingredient">Peanut Butter</td>
                    <td>1 oz</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class="ingredient">Jam/Jelly</td>
                    <td>2 oz</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Spread Jam/Jelly on top of piece bread.
</p>
        <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Spread Peanut Butter on the top of the other piece of bread.
</p>
        <p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Place Jam/Jelly and Peanut butter pieces of bread together so that the Peanut Butter and Jelly sides form the middle.
</p>
<a href="#Contents">Back to Contents</a>
        <h2 id="recipe3">Recipe #3: Steak and Potatoes</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 25 min</li>
            <li>Serves: 1</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td class="ingredient">Steak</td>
                    <td>1-16 oz</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class="ingredient">Russet Potatoes</td>
                    <td>3-6 oz</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Place Steak on grill on high heat until internal color preference is reached.
</p>
        <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Place Potato in oven at 350 for 1 hour.
</p>
        <p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Combine ingredients on plate and consume.  Add sauces and butter as desired.
</p>
